I"Ú<ol>
  <li>Heat the oil in a large deep frying pan over medium heat. Add the pork and cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes or until golden.</li>
  <li>Add the leek and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add the witlof and cook, stirring, for 3-4 minutes.</li>
  <li>Add the cabbage, vinegar and mustard. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, for 2-3 minutes or until the cabbage wilts and the witlof is tender.</li>
  <li>Season with salt and pepper to serve.</li>
</ol>
